[[PageOutline]]
= Claypool Api Core =
== Exceptions ==

Claypool tries to help regulate errors by providing a simple way to extend and identify errors regardless of there position in the hierarchy (like python or java etc).

=== Error ===

This class serves as the basis for all Claypool defined errors.

{{{
try{ 
    throw new Claypool.Error(); 
}catch(e){ 
   if(e.name.match("Claypool.Error")){ 
       //This will be true 
   } 
} 
}}}


=== !ConfigurationError ===

!ConfigurationError can occur when trying to load a configuration by any class extending the Claypool.Factory.
{{{
try{ 
    throw new Claypool.ConfigurationError(); 
}catch(e){ 
   if(e.name.match("Claypool.ConfigurationError")){ 
       //This will be true 
   } 
   if(e.name.match("Claypool.Error")){ 
       //This will be true 
   } 
} 
}}}

=== !NameResolutionError ===

!NameResolutionError can occur when trying to resolve a string to an object using Claypool.resolveName.
{{{
try{ 
    throw new Claypool.NameResolutionError(); 
}catch(e){ 
   if(e.name.match("Claypool.NameResolutionError")){ 
       //This will be true 
   } 
   if(e.name.match("Claypool.Error")){ 
       //This will be true 
   } 
} 
}}}